Three Blind Mice - collectively refered to as Wharf Rat:<br><br>
&quot;Adios, mi amigos and amiga's&quot; is in error.  amiga's is singular and possessive..should be amigas..<br><br>
&quot;Adios&quot; is an expression of farewell that means literally..to God..(Since you mock God..is this supposed to be an implied blessing or a Spatz curse?) <br><br>
&quot;mi&quot; means my but should be plural...mis amigos..<br><br>
The more simple words in any language are the conjunctions, i.e., &quot;and&quot; is expressed as &quot;y&quot;<br><br>
It should have been written..Adios, mis amigos y mis amigas..spoken, it is generally expressed Adios, amigos (including both genders)<br><br>
&quot;Chow&quot; means food for rednecks and Marines..Ciao, in Italian means hello or goodbye (a good phrase for you to master since you don't know whether you are coming or going)..In Spanish the spelling is Chau..pronounced chow..but only means goodbye.<br><br>
At least you are consistent.  In your attempts to be grandiose..suggesting to all that you are some sort of linguist...again, you come across as a fake!<br><br>
Dag, Flikker, Geperverteerde, en Idioot. Dutch for Goodbye, Fag, Pervert and Idiot.<br><br>
Auf Wiedersehen, Bursche,Pervertierte, und Idiot, says the same in German.<br><br>
Au revoir, means to see you ..again. Revoir meaning re-see..or re-view.  Since you are incapable of seeing things the first time, I find it hard to believe that you could see something the second time.<br><br>
Hau, Winkte, Wanyaka, Tuwena Icun'sni, Onze Wicahupo..is a stronger, more foul version in Lakota (that's Sioux).<br><br>
Your greatest error is assuming that you have friends here! Are you prone to driving down the road waving at telephone poles?  Paging yourself at airports?  Feeling self important?<br><br>
There are many expressions that people use when they part..my favorite for you is &quot;Good Riddance!&quot;<br><br>
issKay yMay saSay..pig latin for kiss my ass..had to throw that in..if you don't use languages..you lose'em.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
P.S.  Who were you calling &quot;friend&quot; on this site?  As far as I can determine...everyone views you with contempt or pity or both!
